reviewText: I love these guys! They are so passionate about the music. Beethoven's 5 Secrets is so beautiful--I had tears listening to it, & Steven Sharp Nelson did, too. He & Jon Schmidt use their creative energies & amazing talents to combine different genres of music  (pop/classical) with unique video to produce gorgeous results for ears & eyes.
Title: The Piano Guys: Live at Red Butte Garden

reviewText: Great concert performed at a Utah location.  Watched it on a PBS station one night and had to have it!
Title: The Piano Guys: Live at Red Butte Garden

reviewText: The Piano Guys have an awesome sound and have created amazing arrangements of familiar tunes. This live concert is a treat for those of us that love their sound and wish we could make it to a live concert!
Title: The Piano Guys: Live at Red Butte Garden

reviewText: All of these clips are now on YouTube but on the DVD there are of course no ads or pitches from Jon and Stephen. I have a ticket to see them in 2 weeks. I was hoping for something that I had not yet seen, but I can watch these Guys over and over without getting tired of them. If there had been even one that I had not already seen then I would rate it with 5 stars.
Title: The Piano Guys: Live at Red Butte Garden

reviewText: anything from these guys is fantastic and to think they started on YouTube. Why nobody discovered them I have no clue. But just listen to the arrangement of Beethoven's 9th and Secrets and you will hear just music!
Title: The Piano Guys: Live at Red Butte Garden

reviewText: Just love the The Piano Guys from beginning to end. Great music. Great sound quality. Need I say more.
Title: The Piano Guys: Live at Red Butte Garden

reviewText: I love to watch these guys, the joy as they play the instuments. I think young people who watch this are going to be inspired to get involved in playing a musical instrument. Great video, wish it were longer.
summary: A Excellent evening with great music
Title: The Piano Guys: Live at Red Butte Garden
